_json.gridTitle: A comfortable and luxurious bed and breakfast accommodation set in the ancient High Street of Chipping Campden
_json.description: Badgers Hall is the quintessential English Tea Room which has established the highest reputation for freshly made food  mouth watering cakes.A Step back in time.Situated in the beautiful old Cotwolds market town of Chipping Campden.The building is of honey colored Cotswold stone dating from the 15th century w/ mullioned windows  exposed beams.It stands almost opposite the historic market hall built in 1627 by Sir Baptist Hicks for the sale of local produce.
